          <li><strong>Law and Society</strong><br><span class="xpander">The Bachelor of Arts in gives undergraduates an interdisciplinary liberal arts approach to the study of legal and law-like relationships and institutions. It aids students in developing critical thinking about law and social institutions, as well as critical reading and writing skills, oral communication and listening abilities, and general research skills. It is offered only in combination with other majors: 
            <ul class="tight"> 
