          <li><strong>Public Policy</strong><br><span class="xpander">The Bachelor of Arts is designed to teach students to critically analyze current public policies, their implementation, and their impacts on households, community, and society. Courses draw on developments in philosophy, economics, and political science, amongst others. This <a href="http://www.publicpolicy.ucr.edu/">interdisciplinary major</a> is offered in the <a href="http://chass.ucr.edu/">College of Humanities, Arts, and Social Sciences</a>. </span></li> 
